<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-22T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2614</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-22T20:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1916, 8 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 23, 3.20 p.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3790. On account of Easter holidays rendering consultation of
                                Government with prominent public and business men difficult, think
                                reply of Germany will not come for some time. Think German
                                Government quite surprised by strength of proofs of torpedoing of
                                    <hi rend="italic">Sussex</hi>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>